            "text": " When  $\\Omega = \\mathbb{S}^{n-1}$ , we denote  $W(g) = W(\\mathbb{S}^{n-1}, g)$  the corresponding Wulff-shapes. See for instance [\\[SSZ2, Theorem 1.1\\]](#page-9-1) where Wulff-shape perturbations (with  $\\Omega = \\mathbb{S}^{n-1}$ ) were used to derive a characterization of *n*-simplices as the only convex bodies K such that  $G_K \\geq 0$ , where  $G_K$  is the multi-linear form on  $(\\mathcal{K}^n)^n$  defined by  $G_K(A_1, ..., A_n) = V_n(A_1, K[n-1])V_n(K, A_2, ..., A_n) - V_n(A_1, ..., A_n)V_n(K)$ .",
