            "text": " **Lemma 1** (Alexandrov's variational lemma for mixed volume). Assume  $K$  is a convex body,  $supp(S_K) \\subset \\Omega$ , and  $f \\in C(\\Omega, \\mathbb{R})$ . Denote  $W_t = W(\\Omega, h_K + tf), t \\in \\mathbb{R}$ . Denote  $V_1(t) = V_n(W_t, K[n-1])$ . Then  $(t \\mapsto V_1(t))$  is differentiable<sup>5</sup> at 0, and :",
